==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1600. From {{etyl|la}} {{term|abstemius|abstēmius|abstaining from wine|lang=la}}; from {{term|ab||lang=la}}, {{term|abs||from|lang=la}} + {{term|temus|tēmus|lang=la}}, root of {{term|temetum|tēmētum|[[intoxicating]] drink, mead, wine|lang=la}}, akin to {{etyl|de}} {{term|damlich|dämlich|stupid, silly|lang=de}}, {{etyl|non}} {{term|tham|thām|mugginess|lang=non}}, {{etyl|sga}} {{term|tam|tām|death|lang=sga}}, {{etyl|sa}} {{term|tamyati|tāmyati|he becomes stunned, exhausted|lang=sa}}. {{rfscript|Deva|lang=sa}}

